'''Magister''' was the position [[Leor Hal]] established in [[89 BBY]] to serve as leader of the [[Ferroan]] and [[Langhesi]] settlers of [[Zonama Sekot/Legends|Zonama Sekot]]. Hal himself served as Magister from that point until his death, when his son succeeded him as Magister. When the [[Unidentified Magister|Magister]] was killed during the [[First Battle of Zonama Sekot]], a holographic image of him created by [[Zonama Sekot/Legends|Zonama Sekot]] served as Magister.<ref name=":0">''[[Rogue Planet]]''</ref> At some point between [[29 BBY/Legends|29 BBY]] and [[28 ABY/Legends|28 ABY]], Leor Hal's granddaughter, [[Jabitha Hal|Jabitha]], became Magister.

In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]] the genetic terrorist, [[Zeta Magnus]], established a leading position on the planet [[Skye/Legends|Skye]], the [[Magister of Skye]]. A [[Zeta Magnus (clone)|cloned decoy of Magnus]] held the title for his short rule of the planet before being slain by [[Halagad Ventor]].<ref name="SkyeWalkers">[[SkyeWalkers: A Clone Wars Story]]</ref>

The title continued to be used after Zonama Sekot became the [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] of the [[Yuuzhan Vong]], with [[Danni Quee]] and the [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] [[Tahiri Veila]] and [[Tekli]] being the three possible choices to take over for Jabitha when she died. Although the Magister was of high authority, he/she had no control over the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] itself.

'''Magister''' was the title held by [[Darth Plagueis/Legends|Hego Damask]], the head of the financial lobbying group [[Damask Holdings/Legends|Damask Holdings]].<ref name="Darth Plagueis novel">[[Darth Plagueis (novel)|''Darth Plagueis'']]</ref> The title generally implied "someone of accomplishment, of dignity and bearing ... [an] impressive ... personality."<ref name=":0" />

==Behind the scenes==
The events of ''[[Star Wars: The Dark Nest Trilogy]]'' bring Tahiri Veila and Tekli back into the fold of the New Jedi Order while Danni Quee resigned from the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] to continue her studies on Zonama Sekot.

